</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="525" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[675,1211,685,842]" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">
DIAGNOSIS. — Among the South American 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Melanoplinae">Melanoplinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cigliano &amp; Pocco &amp; Lange, 2011" authorityName="Cigliano &amp; Pocco &amp; Lange" authorityYear="2011" box="[723,837,712,735]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Tiyantiyana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[723,837,712,735]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Tiyantiyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[844,912,712,736]" pageId="2" pageNumber="525" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is characterized by the unique shape of the aedeagus with the ventral valves very long, protruding beneath the pallium, highly surpassing the level of the epiproct, sheath of aedeagus with numerous spines (
<figureCitation box="[747,802,817,842]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Figs 1</figureCitation>
I-L; 4C-D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="530" pageId="2" pageNumber="525" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[677,1209,882,971]" box="[677,821,882,908]" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[677,1209,882,971]" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Small sized apterous insects.Body colour highly variable with multiple short carinulae on tegument.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[674,1212,1008,1700]" lastBlockId="7.[111,648,216,495]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="530" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis box="[677,738,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Males</emphasis>
Head globed-shape, fastigium declivent, with lateral carinae weakly indicated, rounded at the joint of frontal costa; eyes subcircular (
<figureCitation box="[978,1034,1103,1129]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Figs 1</figureCitation>
A-C; 4A). Lateral foveolae of fastigium visible from above (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1194,1134,1161]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Antennae short, shorter than head and pronotum, with flattened segments (
<figureCitation box="[934,1012,1198,1224]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1021,1057,1198,1224]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[113,124,1657,1674]" captionTargetBox="[127,1196,224,1576]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[127,1196,215,1576]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 4. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen., n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, female habitus, lateral view; C, D, endophallic plates, cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, lateral and dorsal views; E, epiphallus, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166917/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">4A</figureCitation>
). Pronotal disk flat, trapezoidal, weakly constricted at the middle; lateral and mid longitudinal carinae weakly indicated; transverse sulci not indicated on pronotal disk, only evident on lateral lobes of pronotum; hind margin emarginated (
<figureCitation box="[815,892,1356,1382]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Fig.1C</figureCitation>
). Meso, metanoto and abdominal tergites with lateral carinulae at the sides of mid longitudinal carina. Prosternal process collar-shaped. Cerci conical,width tapering towards the apex,barely reaching the tip of epiproct (
<figureCitation box="[979,1095,1483,1510]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Fig. 1D, E</figureCitation>
). Epiproct triangular;furculae not developed(
<figureCitation box="[1022,1100,1515,1541]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Fig.1D</figureCitation>
). Abdominal terminalia swollen and upcurved.Pallium thick, highly elevated (
<figureCitation box="[837,913,1578,1604]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Fig.1E</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate short, with rounded distal margin, with the apex surpassing the tip of epiproct. Legs with femora robust, mostly the hind ones (
<figureCitation box="[786,866,1673,1699]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[875,909,1673,1699]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[113,124,1657,1674]" captionTargetBox="[127,1196,224,1576]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[127,1196,215,1576]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 4. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen., n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, female habitus, lateral view; C, D, endophallic plates, cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, lateral and dorsal views; E, epiphallus, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166917/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">4A</figureCitation>
). Phallic complex (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1154,1673,1699]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="525">Figs 1</figureCitation>
I-M; 4C-E): cingulum with reduced rami, zygoma and apodemes well developed. Basal endophallic plates barely developed comparatively to the apical plates. Valves of aedeagus very long, protruding beneath the pallium, highly surpassing the level of the epiproct, apex bent downwards; sheath of aedeagus covering ⅔ of the valves of aedeagus with numerous spines; arch of cingulum large.Epiphallus with lophi widely developed horizontally.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" startId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" targetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1211,1567,1697]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">
FIG. 1. — 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cigliano &amp; Pocco &amp; Lange" authorityYear="2011" box="[194,370,1567,1584]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Tiyantiyana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sunipenis">
<emphasis box="[194,370,1567,1584]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">Tiyantiyana sunipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
n. gen, n. sp.: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[495,508,1567,1584]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">A</emphasis>
, male habitus, lateral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[739,752,1567,1584]" pageId="3" pageNumber="526">B</emphasis>
, 
