<paragraph blockId="7.[113,648,533,749]" box="[113,193,533,559]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis box="[113,193,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">Females</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,648,533,749]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">
Similar to males, but more robust and with the pronotum constricted at the middle. Tegument with clearly indicated carinulae (
<figureCitation box="[480,568,628,654]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[113,124,1657,1674]" captionTargetBox="[127,1196,224,1576]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[127,1196,215,1576]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 4. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen., n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, female habitus, lateral view; C, D, endophallic plates, cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, lateral and dorsal views; E, epiphallus, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166917/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Head with fastigium more prominent; eyes subtrigonal (
<figureCitation box="[122,205,691,717]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">Figs 1F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[219,253,691,717]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[113,124,1657,1674]" captionTargetBox="[127,1196,224,1576]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[127,1196,215,1576]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 4. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen., n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, female habitus, lateral view; C, D, endophallic plates, cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, lateral and dorsal views; E, epiphallus, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166917/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">4B</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor valves strong and long, with serrate margins (
<figureCitation box="[348,435,723,749]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,1567,1584]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,216,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[155,1168,215,1500]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 1. — Tiyantiyana sunipenis n. gen, n. sp.: A, male habitus, lateral view; B, C, male head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; D, E, male distal abdominal segments, dorsal and lateral views; F, G, female head and pronotum, lateral and dorsal views; H, female ovipositor valves;I, phallic complex,lateral view;J, L, endophallic plates,cingulum and aedeagal valves with sheath, dorsal and lateral views; K, distal portion of aedeagus and aedeagal valves, ventral view; M, epiphallus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: Ap, apodemes of cingulum; Ar, arch of aedeagus; Av, aedeagal valves; Ep, endophallic plates;L, lophi of epiphallus; Rm, rami; Sh, sheath of aedeagus, Zy, zygoma. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5166902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5166902/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[111,649,787,1415]" box="[113,277,787,813]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">RELATIONSHIPS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[111,649,787,1415]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">
Despite the lack of the spur on the prosternum (that may be related to the apterism condition), 
<taxonomicName authority="Cigliano &amp; Pocco &amp; Lange, 2011" authorityName="Cigliano &amp; Pocco &amp; Lange" authorityYear="2011" box="[115,239,882,907]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Tiyantiyana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[115,239,882,907]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">Tiyantiyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[242,314,882,908]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares the remaining diagnostic characters of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[421,576,913,939]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Melanoplinae">Melanoplinae</taxonomicName>
: frons convex, profile of face and fastigium united in the same curve; male abdominal terminalia swollen and upcurved, palium coriaceous; male phallic complex with the middle part of the endophallic sclerites constituted by one dorso-lateral piece; cingulum with arch clearly developed. Based on the morphological evidence it was not possible to assign the genus to any of the three tribes described for the South American 
<taxonomicName box="[291,439,1198,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Melanoplinae">Melanoplinae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="AMEDEGNATO C. &amp; CHAPCO W. &amp; LITZENBERGER G." pageId="7" pageNumber="530" pagination="115 - 119" refId="ref10910" refString="AMEDEGNATO C., CHAPCO W. &amp; LITZENBERGER G. 2003. - Out of South America? Additional evidence for a shouthern origin of melanopline grasshoppers. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 29: 115 - 119." type="journal article" year="2003">
Amédégnato 
<emphasis box="[595,637,1198,1224]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="CARBONELL C. S. &amp; CIGLIANO M. M. &amp; LANGE C. E." box="[179,399,1229,1256]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" refId="ref11155" refString="CARBONELL C. S., CIGLIANO M. M. &amp; LANGE C. E. 2006. - Acridomorph (Orthoptera) species of Argentina and Uruguay / Especies de Acridomorfos (Orthoptera) de Argentina y Uruguay. CD-ROM. Publications on Orthopteran Diversity. The Orthopterists' Society at the Museo de La Plata." type="book" year="2006">
Carbonell 
<emphasis box="[286,334,1229,1255]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="Hebard, 1924" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1924" box="[414,642,1229,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Jivarini">Jivarini Hebard, 1924</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rehn &amp; Randell, 1963" authorityName="Rehn &amp; Randell" authorityYear="1963" box="[111,476,1261,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dichroplini">Dichroplini Rehn &amp; Randell, 1963</taxonomicName>
and Parascopini 
<bibRefCitation author="RONDEROS R. A." box="[111,299,1293,1319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref12073" refString="RONDEROS R. A. 1983. - Notas sobre Melanoplinae neotropicales (Orthoptera, Acrididae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 42 (1 - 4): 131." type="journal article" year="1983">Ronderos, 1983</bibRefCitation>
. However, molecular analyses currently underway have shown that 
<taxonomicName authority="Cigliano &amp; Pocco &amp; Lange, 2011" authorityName="Cigliano &amp; Pocco &amp; Lange" authorityYear="2011" box="[522,648,1325,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Tiyantiyana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[522,648,1325,1350]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">Tiyantiyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[113,193,1357,1383]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is grouped with the remaining Andean melanoplines genera (unpublished observations).
</paragraph>
